\f1\b0 When the woman saw that the fruit of the tree was good for food and pleasing to the eye, and also desirable for gaining wisdom, she took some and ate it. She also gave some to her husband, who was with her, and he ate it.\'a0\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 This is so powerful here.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 There are three\'a0types of sins described in the book of 1 John - lust of the flesh, lust of the eyes, pride of life\uc0\u8232 \
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 They are all three here.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Good for food - lust of the flesh\uc0\u8232 \
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Pleasing to the eyes - Lust of\'a0the eyes\uc0\u8232 \
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Desirable for gaining wisdom - pride of life - I want to be like God!\uc0\u8232 \
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 But in this verse also we see the focus\'85it\'92s her and not God and the is another small subtle shift that takes place\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0\cf5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 The shift isn\'92t from God to 
\f0\b Satan
\f1\b0 \'85it\'92s from God to 
\f0\b YOU
\f1\b0 .\cf2 \strokec2  \'a0\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 As long as we keep thinking it\'92s the first we will justify our actions thinking I\'92m not doing anything wrong\'85but if we aren\'92t doing the right thing then it is the wrong thing. \'a0It was pleasing to HER eyes, HER desires, and HER imagination of what it would be like to eat it. \'a0\uc0\u8232 \
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 You are your biggest enemy and we have a culture right now that is telling everyone to figure out who you are and what makes you happy and how do you become the best version of you\'85and nothing is more destructive than this.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 But more importantly Satan is questioning something else\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0\cf5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Satan is questioning God\'92s 
\f0\b DESIGN
\f1\b0  against your 
\f0\b DESIRES
\f1\b0 .\cf2 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Satan is questioning a God who would create something Eve would want, put it in front of her, then tell her not to take it into her own hands. \'a0This is us today. \'a0I hear all the time, this is how God made me, this is just who I am, God wants me to be happy, this will make me happy. \'a0\uc0\u8232 \
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Why would God give me that desire if He didn\'92t want me to act on it? \'a0And anytime someone says something like this you need to know it\'92s from Satan, not God.\
